---
// src/pages/hidden.astro
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Ambiguous Optical Illusions & Hidden Figures | Optical Illusion Lab" 
  description="Explore 10 classic ambiguous and hidden figure illusions. Test your perception, challenge your brain's interpretation, and beat your personal best times."
>

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-900 via-slate-950 to-slate-900 text-white border-b border-indigo-500/10">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top_right,rgba(147,51,234,0.08),transparent_50%)]"></div>
    <div class="absolute -top-40 -left-40 h-80 w-80 rounded-full bg-purple-600/10 blur-3xl"></div>
    
    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center space-y-6">
      <nav class="flex justify-center text-xs font-semibold text-purple-400 space-x-2" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="hover:underline hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-slate-400">Ambiguous Figures</span>
      </nav>
      
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-6xl font-black tracking-tight text-white">
        Ambiguous Figures
      </h1>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-300 leading-relaxed font-medium">
        These aren't magic tricks. They're AMBIGUOUS FIGURES — images 
        your brain can interpret in two completely valid ways. Neither 
        interpretation is wrong. Your brain is just choosing. The 
        question is: can you make it choose differently?
      </p>

      <div class="inline-flex items-center space-x-2 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/45 px-5 py-3 text-xs font-bold text-purple-300 shadow-lg shadow-purple-900/10 max-w-xl mx-auto backdrop-blur-sm">
        ⏱️ Game Rules: Click "I See It!" / "Found It!" as soon as you spot both interpretations to save your time.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content Grid -->
  <main class="py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-16">
      
      <!--
      <!-- Illusion 1. My Wife and My Mother-in-Law -->
      <section class="illusion-container bg-white dark:bg-slate-900/40 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 p-8 shadow-sm flex flex-col gap-6 max-w-[800px] w-full mx-auto relative overflow-hidden" data-id="wife-mother-in-law">
        
        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="w-full space-y-4 text-center">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
              <span class="text-xs font-bold px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-yellow-500/10 text-yellow-500 border border-yellow-500/25">🟡 Medium</span>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider">Ambiguous</span>
            </div>
            <button class="share-btn p-2 rounded-lg bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 text-slate-400 hover:text-purple-400 transition-colors z-20" data-name="My Wife and My Mother-in-Law">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path d="M15 8a3 3 0 1 0-2.977-2.63l-4.94 2.47a3 3 0 1 0 0 4.319l4.94 2.47a3 3 0 1 0 .895-1.789l-4.94-2.47a3.027 3.027 0 0 0 0-.74l4.94-2.47C13.456 7.68 14.19 8 15 8Z"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
          
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1. My Wife and My Mother-in-Law</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-650 dark:text-slate-400 max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed font-semibold">
            One of the most famous ambiguous figures in history. A single drawing depicts both a young lady facing away and an old woman looking downwards.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Highlighted Instruction Box -->
        <div class="w-full my-3 flex items-start gap-2 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/10 bg-indigo-500/5 p-3 text-xs text-slate-350 text-left">
          <span class="text-base leading-none">👁️</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-slate-200">👁️ WHAT TO LOOK FOR:</strong> Can you see both? The young woman's chin is the old woman's nose. The young woman's ear is the old woman's eye. The young woman's necklace is the old woman's mouth.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Visual Display -->
        <div class="w-full flex flex-col items-center justify-center bg-slate-150 dark:bg-slate-950/60 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 min-h-[400px]">
          <div class="relative w-full max-w-[400px] h-[300px] flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-full h-full select-none" viewBox="0 0 350 400" id="svg-wife-mother" style="background: #808080; border-radius: 16px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.35);">
            <!-- Background scarf (dark charcoal) -->
            <path d="M 60,80 C 120,30 230,30 290,80 C 340,140 310,240 270,290 C 230,330 150,330 110,290 C 70,240 50,140 60,80 Z" fill="#1e293b" stroke="#0f172a" stroke-width="3" />
            <!-- Face silhouette (light gray) -->
            <path d="M 120,110 C 180,80 240,80 260,110 C 280,140 270,210 250,240 C 220,270 170,270 140,240 C 115,200 110,140 120,110 Z" fill="#cbd5e1" stroke="#0f172a" stroke-width="2" />
            <!-- Hair/fur collar (medium-dark gray) -->
            <path d="M 100,270 C 160,290 220,290 260,270 C 280,240 290,200 295,170 L 255,170 C 240,210 210,240 160,230 C 120,220 105,240 100,270 Z" fill="#475569" stroke="#0f172a" stroke-width="2" />
            <!-- Nose (Old woman nose / young woman cheek) -->
            <path d="M 160,170 C 125,185 130,205 145,215 C 160,225 165,215 155,205 C 170,195 175,180 160,170 Z" fill="#94a3b8" stroke="#0f172a" stroke-width="2.5" />
            <!-- Neckband / Mouth (Young necklace / old mouth) -->
            <path d="M 160,240 Q 185,245 210,240" fill="none" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="5" stroke-linecap="round" />
            <!-- Ear / Eye (Young ear / old eye) -->
            <path d="M 205,180 C 200,175 195,180 196,186 C 198,190 205,188 205,180 Z" fill="#f8fafc" stroke="#0f172a" stroke-width="2" />
            <!-- Eyelash / Wrinkle -->
            <path d="M 152,175 Q 148,180 142,185" fill="none" stroke="#0f172a" stroke-width="2" />
            <!-- Feather (white accent) -->
            <path d="M 210,80 Q 230,20 210,5 Q 190,20 210,80 Z" fill="#f1f5f9" stroke="#0f172a" stroke-width="1.5" />
            
            <!-- Diagram Highlights Overlay (Revealed via JS) -->
            <g class="diagram-overlay opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300">
              <!-- Young Woman markers -->
              <circle cx="205" cy="180" r="10" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="2.5" fill="none" />
              <path d="M 160,240 Q 185,245 210,240" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="4.5" fill="none" />
              <text x="225" y="180" fill="#3b82f6" font-size="12" font-weight="900">Young Ear</text>
              <text x="225" y="250" fill="#3b82f6" font-size="12" font-weight="900">Choker Necklace</text>

              <!-- Old Woman markers -->
              <path d="M 160,170 C 125,185 130,205 145,215" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="4.5" fill="none" />
              <circle cx="205" cy="180" r="5" fill="#ef4444" />
              <text x="60" y="170" fill="#ef4444" font-size="12" font-weight="900">Old Large Nose</text>
              <text x="225" y="200" fill="#ef4444" font-size="12" font-weight="900">Old Eye</text>
            </g>
          </svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Controls, Voting, and Stopwatch Time Tracker -->
        <div class="w-full space-y-4 pt-2 flex flex-col items-center text-center">
          
          <!-- Time Tracker Bar -->
          <div class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-3 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-950 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 text-xs">
            <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
              <button class="btn-spot bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-500 text-white font-bold px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg">I See It! ⏱️</button>
              <span class="spot-time font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">0.0s</span>
            </div>
            <div class="text-slate-550 dark:text-slate-400 font-bold">
              Personal Best: <span class="pb-time font-mono text-purple-400">-.-s</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Controls panel -->
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 justify-center">
              <button class="btn-vote bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-500 text-white font-bold text-xs px-4 py-2.5 rounded-xl transition-all shadow" data-vote="young">👱‍♀️ Young Woman first</button>
              <button class="btn-vote bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-500 text-white font-bold text-xs px-4 py-2.5 rounded-xl transition-all shadow" data-vote="old">👵 Old Woman first</button>
              <button class="btn-reveal border border-purple-500/30 text-purple-400 hover:bg-purple-500/10 font-bold text-xs px-4 py-2.5 rounded-xl transition-all">Reveal Outlines</button>
            </div>
            
            <div class="stats-panel hidden w-full p-4 bg-purple-500/5 border border-purple-500/20 rounded-xl text-xs space-y-2">
              <div class="flex justify-between font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
                <span>👱‍♀️ Young Woman: <span class="pct-young">52%</span></span>
                <span>👵 Old Woman: <span class="pct-old">48%</span></span>
              </div>
              <div class="w-full bg-slate-700 h-2 rounded-full overflow-hidden flex">
                <div class="bg-purple-500 h-full bar-young" style="width: 52%;"></div>
                <div class="bg-indigo-400 h-full bar-old" style="width: 48%;"></div>
              </div>
              <p class="text-[10px] text-slate-400 italic">Which one you see first may depend on your age! Fun fact: younger viewers usually spot the young woman first.</p>
            </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Collapsible Explanation -->
        <details class="w-full mt-4 border-t border-slate-800/40 pt-3 text-xs text-slate-400 select-none text-left">
          <summary class="font-bold cursor-pointer hover:text-purple-400">👁️ Reveal Answer & Science</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 font-normal leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
            My Wife and My Mother-in-Law is one of the most famous bistable ambiguous figures. Popularized by cartoonist W. E. Hill in 1915, the drawing contains both a young woman facing away into the background and an old woman looking downward in profile. The visual cortex experiences a rivalry between the two interpretations because the same line segments represent different facial features in each version: the young woman's chin functions as the old woman's nose, the young woman's ear acts as the old woman's eye, and the young woman's necklace is perceived as the old woman's mouth. This demonstrates that object recognition is a top-down prediction process.
          </p>
        </details>

        <!-- Explore Link -->
        <div class="w-full mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-slate-500/10 flex justify-between items-center text-xs font-black text-purple-650 dark:text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-500 transition-colors">
          <span>Explore Full Science & Facts</span>
          <a href="/illusions/wife-mother-in-law" class="hover:underline">Explore &rarr;</a>
        </div>

      </section>

      <!-- Illusion 2. All is Vanity -->
      <section class="illusion-container bg-white dark:bg-slate-900/40 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 p-8 shadow-sm flex flex-col gap-6 max-w-[800px] w-full mx-auto relative overflow-hidden" data-id="all-is-vanity">
        
        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="w-full space-y-4 text-center">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
              <span class="text-xs font-bold px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-yellow-500/10 text-yellow-500 border border-yellow-500/25">🟡 Medium</span>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider">Ambiguous</span>
            </div>
            <button class="share-btn p-2 rounded-lg bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 text-slate-400 hover:text-purple-400 transition-colors z-20" data-name="All is Vanity">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path d="M15 8a3 3 0 1 0-2.977-2.63l-4.94 2.47a3 3 0 1 0 0 4.319l4.94 2.47a3 3 0 1 0 .895-1.789l-4.94-2.47a3.027 3.027 0 0 0 0-.74l4.94-2.47C13.456 7.68 14.19 8 15 8Z"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
          
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white">2. All is Vanity</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-650 dark:text-slate-400 max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed font-semibold">
            Created by Charles Allan Gilbert in 1892. This illustration shows a woman sitting at a vanity table, but the overall composition morphs into a giant human skull.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Highlighted Instruction Box -->
        <div class="w-full my-3 flex items-start gap-2 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/10 bg-indigo-500/5 p-3 text-xs text-slate-350 text-left">
          <span class="text-base leading-none">👁️</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-slate-200">👁️ WHAT TO LOOK FOR:</strong> Squint your eyes or step back from the screen. The round vanity mirror forms the skull dome; the woman's head and reflection form the eye sockets; the makeup bottles on the counter form the teeth.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Visual Display -->
        <div class="w-full flex flex-col items-center justify-center bg-slate-150 dark:bg-slate-950/60 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 min-h-[400px]">
          <div class="relative w-full max-w-[400px] h-[300px] flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-full h-full select-none" viewBox="0 0 200 200" id="svg-vanity">
              <!-- Vanity mirror (Skull head outline) -->
              <circle cx="100" cy="80" r="50" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-200" />
              <!-- Eye sockets (Woman's head and its reflection) -->
              <circle cx="85" cy="85" r="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" class="text-slate-400 dark:text-slate-600" />
              <circle cx="115" cy="85" r="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" class="text-slate-400 dark:text-slate-600" />
              <path d="M 80,85 C 80,75 90,75 90,85" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-200" />
              <path d="M 110,85 C 110,75 120,75 120,85" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-200" />
              <!-- Table / Jaw line -->
              <path d="M 40,140 L 160,140 L 150,175 L 50,175 Z" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-200" />
              <!-- Perfume bottles (Teeth) -->
              <g stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" class="text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-200">
                <line x1="85" y1="140" x2="85" y2="152" />
                <line x1="92" y1="140" x2="92" y2="152" />
                <line x1="100" y1="140" x2="100" y2="152" />
                <line x1="108" y1="140" x2="108" y2="152" />
                <line x1="115" y1="140" x2="115" y2="152" />
              </g>
              
              <!-- Skull Overlay -->
              <g id="vanity-overlay-skull" class="opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300 pointer-events-none">
                <circle cx="100" cy="80" r="50" fill="none" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="3" />
                <path d="M 75,130 L 125,130 L 115,160 L 85,160 Z" fill="none" stroke="#ef4444" stroke-width="3" />
                <text x="100" y="25" fill="#ef4444" font-size="11" font-weight="900" text-anchor="middle">Skull Shape</text>
              </g>
              <!-- Woman Overlay -->
              <g id="vanity-overlay-woman" class="opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300 pointer-events-none">
                <circle cx="85" cy="85" r="16" fill="none" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="2.5" />
                <circle cx="115" cy="85" r="16" fill="none" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="2.5" />
                <text x="100" y="62" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="10" font-weight="900" text-anchor="middle">Woman & Reflection</text>
              </g>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Controls, Voting, and Stopwatch Time Tracker -->
        <div class="w-full space-y-4 pt-2 flex flex-col items-center text-center">
          
          <!-- Time Tracker Bar -->
          <div class="w-full flex items-center justify-between p-3 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-950 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 text-xs">
            <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
              <button class="btn-spot bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-500 text-white font-bold px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg">I See It! ⏱️</button>
              <span class="spot-time font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">0.0s</span>
            </div>
            <div class="text-slate-550 dark:text-slate-400 font-bold">
              Personal Best: <span class="pb-time font-mono text-purple-400">-.-s</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Controls panel -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 w-full max-w-sm">
            <div class="flex w-full gap-2">
              <button class="btn-vote flex-1 bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-500 text-white font-bold text-xs py-2.5 rounded-xl transition-all shadow" data-vote="woman">A Woman 👩</button>
              <button class="btn-vote flex-1 bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-500 text-white font-bold text-xs py-2.5 rounded-xl transition-all shadow" data-vote="skull">A Skull 💀</button>
            </div>
            
            <div class="stats-panel hidden w-full p-4 bg-purple-500/5 border border-purple-500/20 rounded-xl text-xs space-y-2">
              <p class="text-[10px] text-purple-400 font-bold text-left">Your selection: <span class="user-selection text-white"></span></p>
              <div class="flex justify-between font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
                <span>👩 A Woman: <span class="pct-woman">45%</span></span>
                <span>💀 A Skull: <span class="pct-skull">55%</span></span>
              </div>
              <div class="w-full bg-slate-700 h-2 rounded-full overflow-hidden flex">
                <div class="bg-purple-500 h-full bar-woman" style="width: 45%;"></div>
                <div class="bg-indigo-400 h-full bar-skull" style="width: 55%;"></div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex w-full gap-2">
              <button class="btn-toggle-woman flex-1 border border-blue-500/30 text-blue-400 hover:bg-blue-500/10 font-bold text-[10px] py-2 rounded-xl transition-all">Show Woman 👩</button>
              <button class="btn-toggle-skull flex-1 border border-rose-500/30 text-rose-400 hover:bg-rose-500/10 font-bold text-[10px] py-2 rounded-xl transition-all">Show Skull 💀</button>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Collapsible Explanation -->
        <details class="w-full mt-4 border-t border-slate-800/40 pt-3 text-xs text-slate-400 select-none text-left">
          <summary class="font-bold cursor-pointer hover:text-purple-400">👁️ Reveal Answer & Science</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 font-normal leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
            All is Vanity is a classic ambiguous composite drawing created by American illustrator Charles Allan Gilbert in 1892. It depicts a young woman sitting at a vanity mirror, looking at her reflection. However, when viewed from a distance, the entire scene blends to form the shape of a human skull. The round vanity mirror forms the dome of the skull, the woman's head and its reflection form the dark eye sockets, and the perfume bottles and cosmetics on the table form the row of teeth along the jaw. This illusion demonstrates how the visual system groups high-frequency detail (the woman and cosmetics) and low-frequency structures (the skull) differently based on viewing distance and focus.
          </p>
        </details>

        <!-- Explore Link -->
        <div class="w-full mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-slate-500/10 flex justify-between items-center text-xs font-black text-purple-650 dark:text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-500 transition-colors">
          <span>Explore Full Science & Facts</span>
          <a href="/illusions/all-is-vanity" class="hover:underline">Explore &rarr;</a>
        </div>

      </section>

      <!-- Illusion 3. Duck or Rabbit? -->
      <section class="illusion-container bg-white dark:bg-slate-900/40 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 p-8 shadow-sm flex flex-col gap-6 max-w-[800px] w-full mx-auto relative overflow-hidden" data-id="duck-rabbit">
        
        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="w-full space-y-4 text-center">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
              <span class="text-xs font-bold px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-yellow-500/10 text-yellow-500 border border-yellow-500/25">🟢 Easy</span>
              <span class="text-xs font-bold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider">Ambiguous</span>
            </div>
            <button class="share-btn p-2 rounded-lg bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 text-slate-400 hover:text-purple-400 transition-colors z-20" data-name="Duck or Rabbit?">
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path d="M15 8a3 3 0 1 0-2.977-2.63l-4.94 2.47a3 3 0 1 0 0 4.319l4.94 2.47a3 3 0 1 0 .895-1.789l-4.94-2.47a3.027 3.027 0 0 0 0-.74l4.94-2.47C13.456 7.68 14.19 8 15 8Z"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
          
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 dark:text-white">3. Duck or Rabbit?</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-650 dark:text-slate-400 max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed font-semibold">
            First published in Germany in 1892 and popularized by Joseph Jastrow in 1899. A single outline forms either a duck facing left or a rabbit facing right.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Highlighted Instruction Box -->
        <div class="w-full my-3 flex items-start gap-2 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/10 bg-indigo-500/5 p-3 text-xs text-slate-350 text-left">
          <span class="text-base leading-none">👁️</span>
          <div>
            <strong class="text-slate-200">👁️ WHAT TO LOOK FOR:</strong> Observe the two protrusions on the left. Are they a duck's open bill or a rabbit's long ears? Use the hint button to see how seasonal contexts prime your brain.
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Visual Display -->
        <div class="w-full flex flex-col items-center justify-center bg-slate-150 dark:bg-slate-950/60 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 min-h-[300px]">
          <div class="relative w-full max-w-[400px] h-[300px] flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-full max-w-[300px] h-[200px] select-none bg-slate-900 rounded-xl" viewBox="0 0 300 200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <!-- Upgraded high contrast Duck-Rabbit with white fill on dark background -->
              <ellipse cx="160" cy="110" rx="75" ry="55" fill="#ffffff" />
              <ellipse cx="95" cy="100" rx="40" ry="35" fill="#ffffff" />
              <path d="M 58,82 Q 25,72 10,90 Q 18,103 58,100 Z" fill="#ffffff" />
              <path d="M 58,100 Q 25,103 12,120 Q 20,133 58,117 Z" fill="#ffffff" />
              <circle cx="82" cy="86" r="6" fill="#0f172a" />
              <circle cx="82" cy="86" r="3" fill="#ffffff" />
